===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|brouken||to use, enjoy|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|brūcan||to enjoy, brook, use, possess, partake of, spend}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*brūkaną||to enjoy, use}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰrūg-||to enjoy}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|brook|lang=sco}}, {{term|brouk||to use, enjoy|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|brûke||to use|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|gebruiken||to use|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|brauchen||to need, require, use|lang=de}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|fruor||enjoy|lang=la}}. Related to {{l/en|fruit}}.

